Travels through Virginia. [From Theodor de Bry's 'America', Vol. I, 1590, after a drawing of John White]. - caption: ''The Virginian's manner of dancing at their religious festivals'. Engraving of a group Native Indians dancing round a circle of wooden posts, on the top of which are carved hooded human faces. Most of the group are wearing fringed apron-skins; their bodies decorated with body paint, and feathers in their hair. They hold twigs and gourd rattles. Three women in the centre are clasped closely together, facing inwards.'
